(9228, 135, 'faq-repeater_0_faq-title', 'How does debt funding differ from equity funding?'),
(9229, 135, '_faq-repeater_0_faq-title', 'field_651fae7b2b885'),
(9230, 135, 'faq-repeater_0_faq-cntnt', 'Unlike equity funding, which involves selling a portion of ownership in the company, debt funding involves borrowing money that needs to be repaid, typically with interest, without giving up equity in the business.'),
(9231, 135, '_faq-repeater_0_faq-cntnt', 'field_651fae842b886'),
(9232, 135, 'faq-repeater_1_faq-title', 'What are the advantages of debt funding?'),
(9233, 135, '_faq-repeater_1_faq-title', 'field_651fae7b2b885'),
(9234, 135, 'faq-repeater_1_faq-cntnt', 'Debt funding allows businesses to access immediate capital without diluting ownership. It offers flexibility in terms of repayment options, interest rates, and loan durations. Debt funding also helps build a credit history and relationships with lenders.'),
(9235, 135, '_faq-repeater_1_faq-cntnt', 'field_651fae842b886'),
(9236, 135, 'faq-repeater_2_faq-title', 'What are the different types of debt funding in India?'),
(9237, 135, '_faq-repeater_2_faq-title', 'field_651fae7b2b885'),
(9238, 135, 'faq-repeater_2_faq-cntnt', 'There are a number of different types of debt funding available in India, including:\r\n<br>\r\n <br> <strong> Bank loans: </strong> Banks are the most common source of debt funding in India. Bank loans can be secured or unsecured, and they can have fixed or variable interest rates.\r\n                             \r\n<br> <strong> Non-bank financial companies (NBFCs):</strong> NBFCs are another important source of debt funding in India. NBFCs offer a wider range of products than banks, including term loans, working capital loans, and equipment financing.\r\n\r\n<br> <strong> Private credit:</strong> Private credit is a type of debt funding that is provided by private investors, such as family offices and high-net-worth individuals. Private credit typically offers higher interest rates than bank loans or NBFC loans, but it can be a good option for businesses that need quick access to capital<br>\r\n<br><strong>  Alternative investment funds (AIFs): </strong>AIFs are a type of investment fund that is regulated by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI). AIFs can invest in a variety of assets, including debt, equity, and real estate. AIFs can be a good option for businesses that need to raise large amounts of capital.'),
(9239, 135, '_faq-repeater_2_faq-cntnt', 'field_651fae842b886'),
(9240, 135, 'faq-repeater_3_faq-title', 'What is the difference between secured and unsecured debt?'),
(9241, 135, '_faq-repeater_3_faq-title', 'field_651fae7b2b885'),
(9242, 135, 'faq-repeater_3_faq-cntnt', ' Secured debt is debt that is backed by collateral, such as real estate or equipment. Unsecured debt is debt that is not backed by collateral. Secured debt is typically less expensive than unsecured debt, because lenders have a lower risk of losing money if the borrower defaults on the loan.'),
(9243, 135, '_faq-repeater_3_faq-cntnt', 'field_651fae842b886'),
(9244, 135, 'faq-repeater_4_faq-title', ' What is project finance?'),
(9245, 135, '_faq-repeater_4_faq-title', 'field_651fae7b2b885'),
(9246, 135, 'faq-repeater_4_faq-cntnt', 'Project finance is a type of debt financing that is used to finance specific projects, such as construction projects or infrastructure projects. Project finance typically involves a number of different lenders, each of which provides a portion of the financing. Project finance can be a complex and time-consuming process, but it can be a good option for businesses that need to finance large, complex projects.'),
(9247, 135, '_faq-repeater_4_faq-cntnt', 'field_651fae842b886'),
(9248, 135, 'faq-repeater_5_faq-title', ' How is the interest rate determined for debt funding?'),
(9249, 135, '_faq-repeater_5_faq-title', 'field_651fae7b2b885'),
(9250, 135, 'faq-repeater_5_faq-cntnt', 'The interest rate for debt funding is typically based on several factors, including the borrower’s creditworthiness, prevailing market rates, the type and duration of the loan, and the collateral provided (if applicable). Lenders assess these factors to determine the level of risk associated with the loan and set an interest rate accordingly.'),
(9251, 135, '_faq-repeater_5_faq-cntnt', 'field_651fae842b886'),
(9252, 135, 'faq-repeater_6_faq-title', 'Can startups and early-stage businesses access debt funding?'),
(9253, 135, '_faq-repeater_6_faq-title', 'field_651fae7b2b885'),
(9254, 135, 'faq-repeater_6_faq-cntnt', ' Yes, startups and early-stage businesses can access debt funding, although the availability and terms may vary based on the lender’s risk assessment. Startups may need to provide additional collateral, demonstrate a viable business model, and showcase growth potential to secure debt funding.'),
(9255, 135, '_faq-repeater_6_faq-cntnt', 'field_651fae842b886'),
(9256, 135, 'faq-repeater_7_faq-title', ' How long does the debt funding process typically take?'),
(9257, 135, '_faq-repeater_7_faq-title', 'field_651fae7b2b885'),
(9258, 135, 'faq-repeater_7_faq-cntnt', 'The duration of the debt funding process can vary depending on the complexity of the loan, the lender’s internal processes, and the completeness of the borrower’s documentation. It generally involves application submission, due diligence, underwriting, loan approval, and disbursal. The timeline can range from a few weeks to a few months.'),
(9259, 135, '_faq-repeater_7_faq-cntnt', 'field_651fae842b886'),
(9260, 135, 'faq-repeater_8_faq-title', ' How does debt funding impact a company\'s financial statements?'),
(9261, 135, '_faq-repeater_8_faq-title', 'field_651fae7b2b885'),
(9262, 135, 'faq-repeater_8_faq-cntnt', ' Debt funding has an impact on a company’s financial statements. It increases liabilities, which can be seen in the balance sheet as long-term or short-term debt. Additionally, the interest paid on the debt is reflected in the income statement as an expense, reducing the company’s net income. It is essential for businesses to carefully manage their debt levels and ensure that debt funding aligns with their financial goals.'),
(9263, 135, '_faq-repeater_8_faq-cntnt', 'field_651fae842b886'),
