(13584, 959, 'faq-repeater_0_faq-txt', ' What types of NRI accounts does Zerodha offer?'),
(13585, 959, '_faq-repeater_0_faq-txt', 'field_651d3c5f35a34'),
(13586, 959, 'faq-repeater_0_faq-cntnt', 'Zerodha offers two types of NRI accounts: Non-Repatriable (NRO) and Repatriable (NRE) accounts. NRO accounts are for income earned in India, while NRE accounts are for funds remitted from abroad.'),
(13587, 959, '_faq-repeater_0_faq-cntnt', 'field_651d3c6835a35'),
(13588, 959, 'faq-repeater_1_faq-txt', 'What are the documents required to open an NRI account with Zerodha?'),
(13589, 959, '_faq-repeater_1_faq-txt', 'field_651d3c5f35a34'),
(13590, 959, 'faq-repeater_1_faq-cntnt', 'The following documents are typically required to open an NRI account with Zerodha:\r\n<br>\r\n – PAN Card \r\n <br>\r\n– Overseas Address Proof  (Bank Statements, Utility Bills, Govt. ID with Address)<br>\r\n  – Overseas Bank Account Proof\r\n<br>\r\n – Valid Visa\r\n<br>\r\n – Passport\r\n <br>\r\n – Photographs (Passport Size)\r\n  <br>\r\n – NRE/NRO Bank Account Proof ( Cancelled Cheque or Online Statement)'),
(13591, 959, '_faq-repeater_1_faq-cntnt', 'field_651d3c6835a35'),
(13592, 959, 'faq-repeater_2_faq-txt', ' Can an NRI trade in all segments available on Zerodha?'),
(13593, 959, '_faq-repeater_2_faq-txt', 'field_651d3c5f35a34'),
(13594, 959, 'faq-repeater_2_faq-cntnt', 'NRIs can trade in most segments available on Zerodha, including equity delivery, equity intraday, equity futures, equity options, currency futures, and currency options. However, NRIs are not allowed to trade in commodity futures.'),
(13595, 959, '_faq-repeater_2_faq-cntnt', 'field_651d3c6835a35'),
(13596, 959, 'faq-repeater_3_faq-txt', ' How can NRIs fund their Zerodha NRI accounts?'),
(13597, 959, '_faq-repeater_3_faq-txt', 'field_651d3c5f35a34'),
(13598, 959, 'faq-repeater_3_faq-cntnt', ' NRIs can fund their Zerodha NRI accounts through the following methods:\r\n \r\n                                  <br> – Wire Transfer: Funds can be transferred from the NRI’s overseas bank account to Zerodha’s designated bank account.\r\n                                   <br>– NRE/NRO Account: NRIs can transfer funds from their NRE or NRO bank accounts in India.\r\n                                  <br> – PIS Account: If the NRI has a PIS (Portfolio Investment Scheme) account, they can link it with their Zerodha NRI account.\r\n                                   <br>– Zerodha currently works with the following Banks for NRE PIS Accounts:\r\n\r\n                                  <br> 1. HDFC Bank Ltd\r\n                                  <br> 2. Axis Bank Ltd\r\n                                  <br> 3. Indusind Bank Ltd\r\n                                  <br> 4. IDFC First Bank Ltd\r\n                                 <br>  5. Yes Bank Ltd'),
(13599, 959, '_faq-repeater_3_faq-cntnt', 'field_651d3c6835a35'),
(13600, 959, 'faq-repeater_4_faq-txt', ' Are there any specific trading limits for NRI accounts on Zerodha?'),
(13601, 959, '_faq-repeater_4_faq-txt', 'field_651d3c5f35a34'),
(13602, 959, 'faq-repeater_4_faq-cntnt', 'Yes, there are certain trading limits for NRI accounts. The maximum limit for equity investments by NRIs is 10% of the paid-up capital of an Indian company, while the overall limit for NRI investments in the Indian stock market is 24% of the paid-up capital.'),
(13603, 959, '_faq-repeater_4_faq-cntnt', 'field_651d3c6835a35'),
(13604, 959, 'faq-repeater_5_faq-txt', ' Can NRIs apply for an IPO (Initial Public Offering) through Zerodha?'),
(13605, 959, '_faq-repeater_5_faq-txt', 'field_651d3c5f35a34'),
(13606, 959, 'faq-repeater_5_faq-cntnt', ' Yes, NRIs can apply for IPOs through Zerodha, provided they have a valid NRI demat account and a linked bank account.'),
(13607, 959, '_faq-repeater_5_faq-cntnt', 'field_651d3c6835a35'),
(13608, 959, 'faq-repeater_6_faq-txt', '  Does Zerodha provide research and advisory services for NRI clients?'),
(13609, 959, '_faq-repeater_6_faq-txt', 'field_651d3c5f35a34'),
(13610, 959, 'faq-repeater_6_faq-cntnt', ' Zerodha does not provide any research and advisory services.'),
(13611, 959, '_faq-repeater_6_faq-cntnt', 'field_651d3c6835a35'),
(13612, 959, 'faq-repeater_7_faq-txt', ' Can NRIs trade in the derivatives (F&O) segment on Zerodha?'),
(13613, 959, '_faq-repeater_7_faq-txt', 'field_651d3c5f35a34'),
(13614, 959, 'faq-repeater_7_faq-cntnt', ' Yes, NRIs can trade in the derivatives segment on Zerodha, which includes equity futures, equity options, currency futures, and currency options. However, it’s essential to understand the risks associated with derivatives trading before participating in it.'),
(13615, 959, '_faq-repeater_7_faq-cntnt', 'field_651d3c6835a35'),
(13616, 959, 'faq-repeater_8_faq-txt', ' Are there any additional charges or fees for NRI trading accounts on Zerodha?'),
(13617, 959, '_faq-repeater_8_faq-txt', 'field_651d3c5f35a34'),
(13618, 959, 'faq-repeater_8_faq-cntnt', 'Zerodha may have specific charges and fees applicable to NRI trading accounts. It’s recommended to check the latest fee structure and charges on Zerodha’s website or contact their customer support for accurate and up-to-date information.\r\n                                     <br>\r\n                                      <br> NRO Account: 0.5% of Order Value or Rs 100/Order, whichever is Lower.\r\n                                     <br>  NRE Account: 0.5% of Order Value or Rs 200/ Order, whichever is Lower.\r\n                                      <br> NRO F&O: Flat Rs 100 per Order.\r\n                                      <br> Apart from Brokerage their will be statutory charges which will be mentioned on the website and can be seen on the contract notes.'),
(13619, 959, '_faq-repeater_8_faq-cntnt', 'field_651d3c6835a35'),
