(13656, 949, 'pis-repeater_0_nonpis-content', '<h3>NRI PIS account</h3>\r\n<p>Portfolio Investment Scheme or PIS is an RBI scheme for NRIs that enables Non-Residents and PIOs to buy and sell shares on a repatriation basis in Indian stock markets. </p>\r\n<p class=\"para\">Here are the key features of PIS account: </p>\r\n<ul class=\"check_list\">\r\n   <li>The PIS bank account is used only for trading in stock markets in India</li>\r\n   <li>It is only for NRIs for trading in equity segment and not for other investments</li>\r\n   <li>Transactions in a PIS account are reported to RBI</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(13657, 949, '_pis-repeater_0_nonpis-content', 'field_6529082504b69'),
(13658, 949, 'pis-repeater_1_nonpis-content', '<h3>NRI Non-PIS account</h3>\r\n<p>A Non-PIS account is an ordinary NRI savings bank account that allows NRIs to invest in shares of Indian companies on a non-repatriation basis. A non-PIS account opened with any bank in India. </p>\r\n<p class=\"para\">Here are the key features of PIS account: </p>\r\n<ul class=\"check_list\">\r\n   <li>Transactions in this account are not reported to the RBI</li>\r\n   <li>An NRO non-PIS account can be used to invest in equity shares, mutual funds, IPOs, bonds, etc. on a non-repatriation basis  </li>\r\n   <li>Can be opened with any bank in India</li>\r\n</ul>'),
