(14047, 1026, 'faq-repeater_5_faq-content', ' Portfolio Investment Scheme (PIS) is a scheme of reserve bank of India under which -\r\n\r\n                                  Non Resident Indian (NRIs) can purchase/sell shares/convertible debentures of Indian companies on Stock Exchanges under Portfolio Investment Scheme. For this purpose, the NRI/PIO has to apply to a designated branch of a bank, which deals in Portfolio Investment. All sale/purchase transactions are to be routed through the designated branch.'),
